            "id": "1c4c34ea7f1440af94a6a",
            "questionText": "Given that the recession speed of a galaxy is $!$2.85 \\times 10^4\\ \\text{km/s}$!$ and the Hubble Constant is $!$70\\ \\text{km/s/Mpc}$!$, calculate the distance to this galaxy in kilometers. Use the conversion $!$1\\ \\text{Mpc} = 3.26 \\times 10^6 \\ \\text{light-years}$!$ and $!$1 \\ \\text{light-year} = 9.5 \\times 10^{12} \\ \\text{km}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "b247f84e6a2746e4a0a8c",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the key formula that relates the recession speed of a galaxy to its distance using Hubble's Law. Which formula should we use for this step?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "c413a452-cd00-445d-b07a-3c69cb5d60aa",
                        "ae5906b8-745a-436d-8695-00ba2c22369f"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = H_0 d$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$d = v \\times H_0$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\frac{d}{H_0}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "e161011f812f40fabd46c",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that we have the correct relationship, use it to compute the distance in megaparsecs (Mpc) by rearranging the equation to solve for distance. Use the given values: recession speed $!$v = 2.85 \\times 10^4 \\ \\text{km/s}$!$ and Hubble Constant $!$H_0 = 70 \\ \\text{km/s/Mpc}$!$. What is the distance in Mpc?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "407.14"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "Mpc",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "c413a452-cd00-445d-b07a-3c69cb5d60aa",
                        "ae5906b8-745a-436d-8695-00ba2c22369f"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "afba3077717c422993a5f",
                    "stepText": "Now, we need to convert the distance from megaparsecs to kilometers. To do that, we first need the conversion factor from 1 Mpc to kilometers. Identify the correct multiplication expression using the given conversions: $!$1\\ \\text{Mpc} = 3.26 \\times 10^6 \\ \\text{light-years}$!$ and $!$1\\ \\text{light-year} = 9.5 \\times 10^{12} \\ \\text{km}$!$. Which expression correctly represents the conversion from 1 Mpc to kilometers?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "97e4ba3a-38d3-43c2-99e7-b74649b32c41"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$1\\ \\text{Mpc} = 3.26 \\times 10^6 \\ \\text{light-years} \\times 9.5 \\times 10^{12} \\ \\text{km/light-year}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$1\\ \\text{Mpc} = \\frac{9.5 \\times 10^{12} \\ \\text{km}}{3.26 \\times 10^6 \\ \\text{light-years}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$1\\ \\text{Mpc} = 3.26 \\times 10^6 \\ \\text{km} \\times 9.5 \\times 10^{12}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "387bddd14ac2441fb4d3a",
                    "stepText": "Excellent! Finally, convert the distance from Mpc to kilometers by multiplying the distance you obtained in Mpc by the conversion factor (in km/Mpc) from the previous step. What is the distance to the galaxy in kilometers?",
